raw_data.title: IT Intelligence Analyst - Journeyman
raw_data.description: The IT Intelligence Analyst - Journeyman applies advanced analytical skills to gather, interpret, and evaluate data to support IT-driven decision-making processes and organizational objectives related to various systems infrastructure. This role involves collecting and analyzing information from diverse sources, identifying trends and potential IT threats and developing actionable intelligence reports to inform stakeholders and IT teams. They collaborate with stakeholders/ programmers/ IT personnel to refine System data requirements, ensure the accuracy of analysis, and contribute to the development of solutions that address IT challenges. Additionally, they monitor emerging trends and technologies in the IT landscape to provide insights that enhance operational efficiency and strategic planning in matters related to national security and/or mission-critical activities.

raw_data.title: HACS Cyber Intelligence Analyst II
raw_data.description: The Cyber Intelligence Analyst II supports the identification, analysis, and mitigation of cyber threats to safeguard: critical information and/or systems and/or mission critical activities. This role involves protecting national security by monitoring cyber security threat landscapes, collecting and analyzing intelligence from open-source and classified sources, and providing actionable insights to cybersecurity teams about potential threats, persons of interest, and/or strategic targets. They evaluate potential vulnerabilities, assess adversary tactics and techniques, and develop threat assessments to inform organizational IT defense systems and  strategies to combat Cyber Threats. Working closely with cyber defense teams, they assist in incident response efforts and contribute to strengthening the overall  Cyber/ security posture by identifying risks and recommending mitigations based on emerging cyber trends and intelligence findings.
